title: Absolutely fantastic.
text: Absolutely fantastic. While the core concepts of this app manage to remain simple and easy to use, the app does manage to feel alive and full of features. The wondrous, supporting community is a major contributing factor this though. Would defidently recommend that everyone tries this at least once! Only complain is the battery consumption rate...It's too high. Nonetheless, a 5 star rating is a minimum reward for such an amazing app!

title: Private fee
text: Private fee I just down loaded this and the first thing i came up agenst was the small fee to keep my diary private.  Sorry but im using this because im feeling abit down and dont think having to payto keep i diary private is at all on. There are many other good aps out therethat will not charge for anything. Talk about taking advantage of peoplewhen thay are down! I would happily pay for a good app but not like this. If you read other reviews other people feel the same. This is just not on.

title: This app is changing my life.
text: This app is changing my life. This past week I started seeing a psychiatrist and he referred me to this app and one other like it to start logging my moods and feelings throughout the days between our next visits; and this app is changing my life. I've never been the type to keep what would be considered a 'journal', but this app feels like so much more than that. Not only is it simple, intuitive, and straight to the point; it adds a social aspect that allows for instant support for, and from, others. It is a good feeling.

I was honestly really skeptical when I first installed the app but it really exceeded all my expectations. It's easy to use and the word board really helps keep track my dominant moods so I can easily pick them out when I talk to my psychiatrist. The community is friendly and supportive and the anonymous aspect helps ease any feelings of vulnerability.   The only downsides I find are that I can't transfer the app to my SD card and that it has no lock feature but other than that it's great.

title: Such a great community of caring  people
text: Such a great community of caring  people Love this app so much simple yet works. The community of people is amazing you can really see your not alone with what ever your going thru. Plus i love helping people. Cause ive been thru some tough times. If i can make one person smile or wanna live then im happy. Id give it 5 stars if it had a private msg part and you could make a profile. Fix that and you get 5 stars!

title: Life saving app!
text: Life saving app! I love this app. At first I was a little taken aback and shocked that every post was public (unless you pay $$ to post privately). I soon realized what a blessing it is. Just be careful and take all the warnings about your username seriously. Do not use any personal info (like name or birth date) in your username since your posting publicly. The app has a really good community of all walks of life and various ages.

title: Pretty good!
text: Pretty good! I love the ability to write a comment with each mood, to remember the events of the day. I wish the date system worked better - if I forget to track the night before, I'd like to be able to set the date back. At first it seemed like I could, but changing it just screws up their little chart and it still shows the mood on the day I wrote it, not the day I changed it to. This makes long-term comparisons more difficult.

title: just one suggestion
text: just one suggestion really like it, it helps me look back and see if my moods improved over time. Just one suggestion: when I block someone I don't wanna see a single thing they post. I wanna pretend they don't even exist, ya know? If it could be like that that'd be great

title: How greedy can you be?
text: How greedy can you be? A mood tracking app in which your entries are PUBLIC unless you pay for the private version? That's sick. This could so greatly benefit people with mood disorders to record their cycles, but instead it's another money-grabbing social network. I've never been so appalled by an app in my life.

title: Simple and effective
text: Simple and effective I'm using this to track my depression as I'm changing my meds. The interface is easy and intuitive, and the charting is excellent for high-level overviews. The 1-5 granularity is great for not getting inundated with tracking details, which is something I've had problems with in other mood-tracking apps. I appreciate that I can make entries in the past too, as it's not always convenient to make a journal entry when important things happen.

title: Nice!
text: Nice! The interface is nice and easy to use. Color coding is great and so is the option to add a note about each mood you log. Not being able to have a private log with the free version is the only real downside. But, due to the anonymous nature of the app, it doesn't matter too much.

title: Love this
text: Love this It's really helpful. But people are saying it costs money to use a private diary. I use private diaries for all my entries and not once have I been notified about a cost. Is this a glitch? Am I paying for it without knowing? And can someone tell me how much it is please.

title: Helpful
text: Helpful I like being able to track the spikes in my mood, and I like being able to anonymously post my thoughts into the void. It's also cool to see how other people are feeling when you're feeling sad or angry or happy or whatever. Helps remind you that you're not alone, but at the same time you don't have to use up spoons to engage if you don't have the energy for it.

I've liked this app very much and the social support and interacting with other users are very important to me. However, these past days Ive noticed some major problems with this app Ive never had before. I cant get any hearts or comments anymore from the other users. I also cant see my followers nor the people I follod moods anymore. I can see everyone's moods but even the newest of them are a day old. I feel like this app doesnt refresh or sync anymore for some reason. I hope you could fix this bug even by a new update. Please fix this otherwise great app so I dont have to delete it  :(

title: Great,  except...
text: Great,  except... I really like that there is an option for adding a time to a mood entry since my emotional state can change throughout the day. However, the idea of having every entry viewable by anyone via something like a newsfeed makes me incredibly uncomfortable. Having to pay for a privacy option is cruel.

title: It helps
text: It helps I use this to vent, to exclaim my happiness, to say what I cant say in real life. It helps me feel connected with my feelings and the community reminds me that I'm not alone in my thoughts. Theres people who have gone through similar situations that listen to what youre saying and help you in the way they can. I hope you enjoy this as much as I do.((:

title: The best..Just needs password protection
text: The best..Just needs password protection I'm changing my vote to 5 stars. There are still some additional features that would be nice but this app has helped me so much more than I even intended and I don't even utilize the community aspect of it as I am more of a private person. On that note all it needs is a password to get into it so that just anyone can't pick up the phone and read about your information. **update** Something happened and it won't let you read the entries after writing. Frustrating. I will use another app if not fixed soon.

Works ok, but could be more user friendly: The text boxes don't seem to be the native Android text boxes, and it's painfully difficult to move the caret around by tapping in the text when you need to edit something or correct some spelling mistakes. Also, The "mood selection" could be made easier by having a "tag cloud" or dropdown to easily let you select an already stored mood. We'll see how long I can put up with those pesky text boxes.

I can be too private. This is interesting for me (someone who has never used social media!) as it's my private stuff but I'm also putting it out there for others to see and interact with. I'm into it so far. People using it seem supportive.

I thought it was weird that it was public...didn't feel comfortable with that, so I'm grateful for the option to go private, which is worth the $0.99. Thanks for a way to track my ups and downs and all arounds. It'll be good to reflect on later.

Good app. Works as described.   People complaining about a tiny fee to make entries private need to understand making an application takes hard work, don't demand people work for free. The alternative would have been crappy intrusive ads and no one likes those either.

title: Paying for Privacy?
text: Paying for Privacy? Especially with something as personal as moods/feelings (which I wouldn't feel comfortable with sharing publicly, even if it's under a random username). A good concept, but terribly callous (& greedy) of the developer. Extremely disappointed.

Way better than other mood tracking apps for a bunch of reasons: - no pesky ads! - no pressure to buy premium version (like this app being a trial etc.), - highly customisable (the possibility of inputting own moods and rating them), - syncing between multiple devices, - clear mood graph, - anonymity, - the chance to communicate with other members (barely any trolls there). It gets well deserved 5 stars from me.
